<Author>inflatabill
<Content>Shhh, keep this one a secret I read all the reviews, and took a chance. And I'm glad I did.I was working an event at the Nokia theater and needed to be within walking distance of the venue. The hotel is on the same street, about a mile away, which is close enough for me. OK, so the TV channel selection was limited, but I didn't go to LA to watch TV in my hotel room. It was still good enough to unwind before going to bed, and catch up on the news while drinking morning coffee. The underground parking lot was small, but the hotel's lot across the street was never full, even though the hotel was fully booked. The neighborhood wasn't Beverly Hills, but I never felt unsafe, even when walking 2 blocks to Rodeo (which I recommend) for late night Mexican food and margaritas.The room was clean and spacious, and the staff was excellent. I was there for three nights, and every time I went to the desk, they were friendly and professional and made me feel like they really cared about me. They even allowed me to check out late, after having car troubles. I will definitely stay there again. It's my new second home in downtown LA.Did I mention the staff was excellent? 
