<Author>Steve_and_Oonagh
<Content>a great place to stay near downtown L.A. It is hard to find a good hotel near downtown L.A. that doesn't cost $300+ per night. I was pleasantly surprised to find this Clarion to be as nice as it was. Parking was easy and secure, the staff was friendly, the rooms are nicely equipped with good beds, comforters, two kinds of pillows, a quiet refrigerator, microwave and central air conditioning. The good-sized pool area was clean and the water warm. There are two courtyard sitting areas surrounded by the building. The room was quiet and the location is less than a couple of miles from downtown, Staples center and the convention center. They even have a breakfast buffet area ($7.99 per person extra). There are fountains and waterfalls in the lobby area and free, easy, fast internet access (but only in the lobby area). I recommend this hotel for families on vacation or business travelers needing a nice place to stay near downtown L.A. and the price is right, too! 
